news.shortDetail: Rumors spread online about changes in tuition fees.
news.detail: A viral post claimed tuition fees would double starting next year. Officials confirmed this is FALSE and clarified no such policy exists.

news.shortDetail: Social media post warns of a deadly new strain.
news.detail: Experts confirmed a new variant exists, but WHO stated it is not more deadly than existing ones. The viral post exaggerated risks.

news.shortDetail: News about eco-friendly farming practices gains attention.
news.detail: The story is TRUE. The award was presented by the Ministry of Agriculture to support eco-friendly initiatives.

news.shortDetail: A viral video warns of a disaster hitting Southeast Asia.
news.detail: Seismologists confirmed earthquakes cannot be predicted with exact dates. This claim is FALSE.

news.shortDetail: Photos shared of students using AI equipment.
news.detail: TRUE story. The new facility aims to support AI and robotics research with state-of-the-art tools.
Now this game is under control.......
Pollution is the introduction of substances or energy (such as light or heat) into the natural environment in amounts or concentrations that can be harmful for humans, animals, and plants.
